Research the industry-standard quality gate thresholds used by the major commercial and open-source static analysis platforms: SonarQube, Codacy, CodeClimate, and DeepSource. For each platform, identify their default and recommended thresholds for the following metrics: cyclomatic complexity per function, cognitive complexity per function, code duplication percentage, technical debt ratio, maintainability rating bands (A through E or equivalent), and lines of code per function and per class. Document which of these thresholds are configurable versus hardcoded, and what rationale each vendor provides for their chosen defaults. Where published academic or industry studies back these numbers, cite them. Specifically look for the SonarQube Quality Gate documentation, the CodeClimate maintainability rubric, and the Codacy code patterns documentation. Identify where the platforms disagree on thresholds and what reasoning each uses. The goal is to produce a calibration reference that a custom static analysis tool can use to align its severity bands with industry expectations, so include the exact numeric cutoff values used by each platform wherever they are publicly documented.
